**Goal**

The goal of this project is to develop a **secure and efficient Online Examination System** using **PHP Laravel** for the backend and **PostgreSQL** for database management. The system allows an **admin** to manage quiz categories and questions efficiently. Admin authentication ensures secure access, allowing only authorized users to log in. Admins can create, edit, and delete **quiz categories** and **questions**, supporting various formats like **MCQs, true/false, and descriptive questions**. The system securely stores all data in PostgreSQL, ensuring optimized queries for fast performance. Security measures such as **input validation** and session management are implemented to prevent unauthorized access and attacks. Designed with a **modular architecture**, the system is scalable and maintainable, allowing for future enhancements such as **student accounts, automated grading, and real-time result generation**.

## **STEP 3:**  {#step-3:}

**Installing All Dependencies and Setting Up the Environment**

Install PHP & Composer (For Laravel)  
sudo apt update && sudo apt install \-y php php-cli php-mbstring php-xml unzip curl composer

Install Podman (Container Management)  
sudo apt install \-y podman  
podman \--version

 Install PostgreSQL Client (For Local Testing \- Optional)  
sudo apt install \-y postgresql-client

##  Setup Podman Network

podman run \-d \--name exam-db \\  
  \--network exam-network \\  
  \-e POSTGRES\_USER=admin \\  
  \-e POSTGRES\_PASSWORD=admin123 \\  
  \-e POSTGRES\_DB=examdb \\  
  \-v /home/vikram/project/db:/var/lib/postgresql/data \\  
  postgres:latest

#  Setup Laravel Project: {#generate-laravel-application-key}

Install Laravel Dependencies  
composer install

Installing & Configuring JWT Authentication in Laravel  
Installing & Configuring JWT Authentication in Laravel  
Publish JWT Configuration

php artisan vendor:publish \--provider="Tymon\\JWTAuth\\Providers\\LaravelServiceProvider"

Generate JWT Secret Key

php artisan jwt:secret

## 

## **STEP 4:**  {#step-4:}

#### **Configure `.env` File for PostgreSQL**

Open the `.env` file and update the database connection:

DB\_CONNECTION=pgsql

DB\_HOST=laravel\_db

DB\_PORT=5432

DB\_DATABASE=laravel\_db

DB\_USERNAME=laravel

DB\_PASSWORD=secret

##  Generate Laravel Application Key {#generate-laravel-application-key}

php artisan key:generate

## Run Laravel Migrations {#run-laravel-migrations}

php artisan migrate

##    Project  run on localhost:

php artisan serve
